<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id808fc593-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c" identifier="/us/usc/t40/s125"><num value="125">§ 125.</num><heading> Library memberships</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Amounts appropriated may be used, when authorized by the Administrator of General Services, for payment in advance for library memberships in societies whose publications are available to members only, or to members at a lower price than that charged to the general public.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id808fc594-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/217">Pub. L. 107–217</ref>, <date date="2002-08-21">Aug. 21, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1071">116 Stat. 1071</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
